Small #Ebola setback today. Beni reported its first case in 23 days. Seems a woman was infected by a survivor -- possible sexual transmission case, but that detail is not given. The good news is the case was diagnosed. Hopefully there won't be additional cases from it.]

- Thu 21 Feb 2019. Epidemiological situation report, DRC Ministry of Health
[in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://us13.campaign-archive.com/?u=89e5755d2cca4840b1af93176&id=0769f86b80

The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri dated 20 Feb 2019:
-Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 853, of which 788 are confirmed and 65 are probable.
- In total, there have been 531 deaths (466 confirmed and 65 probable).
- 177 suspected cases are under investigation.
- 5 new confirmed cases, including 3 in Katwa, 1 in Kyondo and 1 in Kalunguta.
- 2 new community deaths of confirmed cases in Katwa.

We will start sharing the number of recovered cases as soon as the current database update is complete.

News of the response
Surveillance in Vuhovi
--------------------
- In the past 2 days, there has been a decline in the follow-up of contacts in Vuhovi because of the mourning of health staff and community relays following the kidnapping and assassination of a nurse from the Bisongo health center by a group of unidentified people.
- The Response Coordinator and the WHO Incident Manager in Butembo traveled to Vuhovi to offer their condolences and encourage health professionals in the area to resume the response activities. Health workers have asked that the coordination be sure to increase their security to protect them against the attacks of the uncivil who sow terror in this country. Contrary to certain information that has circulated, the patients of the Vuhovi General Reference Hospital have not been removed and they continue to be cared for onsite.

Vaccination
-----------
- Vaccination of front-line providers has started on a preventive basis in the Lolwa Health Zone between Komanda and Rwampara on the road connecting Beni to Bunia.
- Since the start of vaccination on 8 Aug 2018, 82 144 people were vaccinated. [See the source URL above for numbers vaccinated per township.]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteurs Mary Marshall and Kunihiko Iizuka

